Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)

item.title: Privacy Policy [OLD]
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Our website address is: http://localhost:8888.

What personal data we collect and why we collect it

Comments

When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymised string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Contact forms

Cookies

If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you have an account and you log in to this site, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Analytics

Who we share your data with

How long we retain your data

If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognise and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where we send your data

Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

Your contact information

Additional information

How we protect your data

What data breach procedures we have in place

What third parties we receive data from

What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data

Industry regulatory disclosure requirements

item.title: Home
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
LESSONS

Drum Lessons are Fun, Fulfilling and proven to enhance your mood! Find out what to expect in your Drum Lessons.

Learn More
EXAMS

Pass your Rockschool Drum Grades with our 100% Pass Rate. GCSE, BTEC & A-Level Preperation also catered for.

Learn More
PRICES

A Range of Excellent value for money options to choose from.

Learn More
ABOUT DRUM LESSONS N8

Learn to play drums with a highly qualified drum teacher in North London.

Your drum lessons will be taught by James Bennetts Bmus. With over 10 years professional teaching experience, James is well equiped to deliver engaging one-to-one lessons tailored to meet each student’s individual goals.

Whether you are looking to pick up drumsticks for the first time or refine your Moeller Technique, James has a vast library of teaching materials to achieve those goals.

For students looking to pass their drumming exams, James has a 100% pass rate for Grades 1-8 Rockschool & Trinity Guildhall. He also assists many students prepare for GCSE, BTEC & A-Level performance assesments.

As a Roland Ambassador students of N8 Drum Lessons are entitled to a 25% discount on all Roland drum products.

GET STARTED NOW

What we offer

All lessons are tailored to meet each individual’s requirements & goals. 

BEGINNERS

Having helped hundreds of students pick up drumsticks and start their drumming journey, you will up & drumming straight away. There is a long list of benefits to learning to play drums, and it is a fantastic way to reduce tension, anxiety and stress!

ADVANCED

James has been taught by some of the world’s top educators. He has an in-depth knowledge of advanced techniques and has an extensive library of teaching materials to take your playing to the next level.

ROCKSCHOOL GRADED EXAMS

Drumming grades are a great way to show the world what stage you are at behind the drum kit. We have a 100% pass rate grades 1-8 and an in-depth knowledge of the grading system and marking requirements.

GCSE, BTEC & A-LEVEL PREPERATION

With performance module requirements being very specific & a large proportion of your overall grade, James can help guide you through the syllabus and develop skills inline with the course criteria. 

Drum Lesson Prices

We strive to offer excellent value for money lessons. All prices are inline with Musician’s Union rates and checked against other local music tutors.

30 MINUTES

Recommended for students up to the age of 14 or Grade 2).

£25
45 MINUTES

Recommended for students up to the age of 16 or Grade 4).

£35
60 MINUTES

Recommended for Adults, students aged 16+ or Grade 5+.

£45
EXAM PREPERATION

Every situation is different. Please contact us to discuss your requirements.

Contact

Ready to Drum? Let’s go!

CONTACT US NOW

Contact us

Please contact us with any questions about lessons or additional requirements. We will get back to you as soon as possible.

item.title: 80 days around the world
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
80 days around the world, we'll find a pot of gold just sitting where the rainbow's ending. Time - we'll fight against the time, and we'll fly on the white wings of the wind. 80 days around the world, no we won't say a word before the ship is really back. Round, round, all around the world. Round, all around the world. Round, all around the world. Round, all around the world.
I never spend much time in school but I taught ladies plenty. It's true I hire my body out for pay, hey hey. I've gotten burned over Cheryl Tiegs, blown up for Raquel Welch. Hey there where ya goin', not exactly knowin', who says you have to call just one place home. He's goin' everywhere, B.J. McKay and his best friend Bear. He just keeps on movin', ladies keep improvin', every day is better than the last. New dreams and better scenes, and best of all I don't pay property tax. Rollin' down to Dallas, who's providin' my palace, off to New Orleans or who knows where. Places new and ladies, too, I'm B.J. McKay and this is my best friend Bear.
